-- Acteon Owner First Reserve Plans Sale of Company, Times Reports
-- B y   J e s s e   W e s t b r o o k
-- 2012-04-22T12:13:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-22/acteon-ceo-may-receive-250-million-pounds-from-sale-times-says.html
Acteon Group Ltd. has been put on
the market by First Reserve Corp., a U.S. private-equity firm
with a majority stake, and may fetch about 1 billion pounds
($1.6 billion), the Sunday Times reported, without saying where
it got the information.  A sale of the of the oilfield-services company may earn
about 250 million pounds for Chief Executive Officer Richard Higham, who holds 25 percent of Acteon, the newspaper said.
First Reserve has hired JPMorgan Chase & Co. to find a buyer,
according to the Sunday Times.  An Acteon spokesman declined to comment when contacted by
e-mail today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jesse Westbrook in London at 
